content: Once again an exquisite game by Cotton - the puzzles so inventive, the graphics delightful and music restful - please add many more floors to this elevator!

Awesome game! Short but well worth the money paid. Good storyline too

Outstanding! Easy to finish, hard to get all achievements. If you're easily frustrated by not getting 100% then you may not enjoy the game, but if you like replaying the game and trying many different combinations then it's extremely satisfying to play and gives many hours of entertainment. There are so many subtleties in the expressions of the characters, and the puzzles are very clever. The hardest achievement to get is the "about us" one.

At the point of the Floor 20 I'm bored & tired of this game. I don't enjoy games where I'm randomly clicking around to progress it and only from there figuring out what to do. It feels repetitive, even with the different levels. I've played plenty of hidden object puzzle type games which I love & this one is more annoying than fun. I won't be sad when it ends & yet I love when I'm sad at a games end, since I didn't want it to because I enjoyed it that much. This for me was not that, sadly.
This Is A Fun Game To Play.

Really good game until i encountered a glitch. I'm stuck on mini robot level because only two items show up on the x ray/painting: the snow globe and the feather. Otherwise the screen is empty. Please fix
replyContent: This is actually not a bug. By completing this puzzle you can enter a hidden level. Before that, you need to obtain the key items for the puzzle in previous levels. If you follow the other hint and adjust the mini robot instead, you can continue with the main story.
